4. Prompt 2 — Deep Root Cause Diagnosis
Anti-Pattern Identified
Using range(len(items)) to loop over a list is old-fashioned Python. Every time you write range(len()), you create a risk of off-by-one errors. Modern Python uses enumerate() or direct iteration instead.

Debugging Tools for IndexError
Tool	How to Use
print(len(items))	Add before loop to verify list size
print(i)	Add inside loop to track which index fails
Python debugger pdb	Add: import pdb; pdb.set_trace() before the loop
VS Code debugger	Set a breakpoint on the for loop line and step through

